    "actions_taken": [
      "First aid performed by platform personnel",
      "Evacuation by helicopter to offshore medic",
      "Wound cleaning and bandaging by medic",
      "Transport to clinic for further treatment",
      "Five stitches applied to close wound",
      "Medical reevaluation on 24 March 2020",
      "Placement on restricted/light duty work",
      "BSEE investigation conducted on 26 March 2020"
    ],
    "summary": "On 23 March 2020 at 11:30 hours, a contractor on Main Pass 259 A platform sustained a laceration to his wrist while using a box cutter to remove electrical tape from a flange during hot bolting operations. The contractor cut through his glove and into his wrist using improper cutting technique (cutting towards his body) and was not wearing cut-resistant gloves. The injury required five stitches and resulted in restricted duty for approximately 14 days.",
